    <center><table class="itemDisplayTable">
<tr><td class="metadataFieldLabel">Title:&nbsp;</td><td class="metadataFieldValue">A Study on Tourism Marketing: A Service Marketing Perspective Under DTPC,Malappuram</td></tr>
<tr><td class="metadataFieldLabel">Authors:&nbsp;</td><td class="metadataFieldValue">Mohamed Rubin S.A</td></tr>
<tr><td class="metadataFieldLabel">Keywords:&nbsp;</td><td class="metadataFieldValue">Marketing Perspective</td></tr>
<tr><td class="metadataFieldLabel">Issue Date:&nbsp;</td><td class="metadataFieldValue">1-May-2010 </td></tr>
<tr><td class="metadataFieldLabel">Publisher:&nbsp;</td><td class="metadataFieldValue">SRM University</td></tr>
<tr><td class="metadataFieldLabel">Series/Report no.:&nbsp;</td><td class="metadataFieldValue">P4755</td></tr>
<tr><td class="metadataFieldLabel">Abstract:&nbsp;</td><td class="metadataFieldValue">Man, since the ages unaccounted in the pages of history has been travelling worldwide to explore, conquer or to relocate from time to time. During his travels, man found the joy of seeing new places and experiencing new cultures and countries. Soon by the power of the word of mouth and the innumerable stories that crossed the geographical boundaries got people from all over the world travelling for leisure, business or other purposes. It was common to all countries and gradually due to the invention and development of modern transportation system, tourism has become a very profitable and lucrative source of income for each and every country, no matter big or small; owing to the fact that no two countries are similar in any dimensions. This fact also led to the establishment of generally accepted ideologies that a few countries or cities are far more beautiful and famous than others. With the course of time, these famous locations became the hallmark of tourism and “wonders of the modern world”.
Tourism in India dates back thousands of years when messengers and merchants from distant lands used to come for trade and commerce. Since then foreigners from all civilized lands came to India either to explore or to exploit the vast natural resources of the country. But time has changed, India is now considered as one of the most important tourist destinations in the world. Tourism in India is dependent on the varied geographical and cultural variations across the country. But, in reality it is the effort of each and every small and large village, town and district level tourism operators that make India a tourist haven.
This project is focused on such a small district in the state of Kerala called Malappuram which houses a vast and lush expanse of natural treasure to be highlighted as tourist destination. Kerala is undeniably the most frequented state by tourists from all over the world and also from India within. Kerala has fourteen districts; each different from one another in terms of geography and culture. Some of them are renowned; some aren’t despite being equally beautiful and fortunate of having nature’s abundance.
In this project work, the Malappuram tourism sector has been analyzed and assessed to furnish productive and realistic suggestions to develop the current scenario in the most beneficial way. The foundation of the project is on the concepts of “Marketing the services provided by DTPC in Malappuram District” which allows one to think and refer a place as a brand for the sake of its publicity, acceptance and sustenance.
Malappuram has many operational tourist spots and privileges and a few are being either constructed or renovated. So, it is the best time that the District Tourism Promotion Council (DTPC) of Malappuram gets all the help they can in terms of suggestions, ideas and working procedures.</td></tr>
<tr><td class="metadataFieldLabel">URI:&nbsp;</td><td class="metadataFieldValue"><a href="http://hdl.handle.net/123456789/8322">http://hdl.handle.net/123456789/8322</a></td></tr>
